properties.name: Almost to the Promised Land
properties.description: Posted by MisternaxalBig Pine, CABig Pine is the town you\'ll find at the junction of 168 and 395, the highway that runs the length of the Owens Valley...and that took me north to Bishop, CA.

properties.name: Casa Galaviz
properties.description: Posted by Misternaxal508 South Elm St.,Denton,TXIf you haven\'t had Casa Galaviz breakfast tacos, you haven\'t had breakfast tacos. They could boil dirty shoelaces and wrap them in their heavenly tortillas and they\'d taste incredible!

properties.name: Eugene, Oregon & Vicinity
properties.description: Posted by MisternaxalEugene, OregonVisiting next month and visiting for the Oregon Country Fair this summer!

properties.name: Greenhouse Restaurant
properties.description: Posted by Misternaxal 600 North Locust St., Denton, TXOne of the two best places in town to support local businesses and have some upscale food.

properties.name: Harer, Ethiopia
properties.description: Posted by MisternaxalEthiopiaWalled city in eastern Ethiopia famous for coffee, hyenas and where my uncle taught during his time in the Peace Corps. I hope to visit sometime in the next two years.

properties.name: Heading Into Something Better
properties.description: Posted by MisternaxalLida, NevadaBeginning around Lida on Highway 266, you head into the mountains for the first of many ups and downs crossing the White Mountain range as you leave Nevada and enter California.

properties.name: International Foods
properties.description: Posted by Misternaxal 609 Sunset Street, Denton, TXVery tasty Mediterranean/Middle Eastern/Persian food served up by a very nice Persian family. Best lamb kebab I\'ve had outside of Chicago.

properties.name: Jena, Germany
properties.description: Posted by MisternaxalJena, GermanyGotta get over there in the summer or fall!

properties.name: Kreuz Market
properties.description: Posted by Misternaxal 619 N. Colorado St., Lockhart, TXNo BBQ run to Central Texas is complete without a trip to Kreuz Market.

properties.name: Long Trail Brewing Company
properties.description: Posted by Misternaxal Bridgewater Corners, VTLong Trail Brewing produces some of the best beer you\'ll ever have...plus they have one very scenic location at Bridgewater Corners, the intersection of Routes 4 and 100A.

properties.name: Louie Mueller's BBQ
properties.description: Posted by Misternaxal205 West Second Street, Taylor, TXYou think you\'ve had BBQ? If you haven\'t had Louie Mueller\'s, you haven\'t had BBQ.

properties.name: Lovejoys Tap Room & Brewery
properties.description: Posted by Misternaxal 604 Neches St., Austin, TXOne of the best places to enjoy some Texas-brewed suds anywhere in the state!

properties.name: Magic Hat Brewing Company
properties.description: Posted by Misternaxal5 Bartlett Bay Rd, South Burlington, VTSome of the best beer and most awesome people in the world!

properties.name: Mammoth Lakes, Inyo National Forest
properties.description: Posted by Misternaxal Bishop, CAGoing to visit Inyo this summer with an eye to getting up to Mammoth Lakes and, if there\'s time, making it down to King\'s Canyon and Sequoia.

properties.name: McCarran Airport
properties.description: Posted by MisternaxalLas Vegas, NevadaI flew into Las Vegas on June 28th, rented a car and got the hell out of Dodge, making a quick detour down The Strip to take some pictures.

properties.name: Rasoi - The Indian Kitchen
properties.description: Posted by MisternaxalDenton, TXDenton\'s finest Indian food, and not just because it\'s the only Indian restaurant in town! The folks who run Rasoi are awesome and the food is very, very good. Look for the former gas station called the Syber Stop and you\'ll find Rasoi.

properties.name: Reunited And It Feels So Good
properties.description: Posted by MisternaxalBishop, CAI met up with Laura and her friend Suzanne in Bishop, a town in high mountain desert bounded by the White Mountains to the east and the snow capped Sierras to the west.

properties.name: Splendid Isolation
properties.description: Posted by MisternaxalDeep Springs, CAYou have to see Deep Springs to really appreciate it. As you climb down from your first mountain pass in the White Mountains, you find yourself looking out across this dichotomy of the arid and the verdant.

properties.name: That Shit's Real, Man!
properties.description: Posted by MisternaxalIndian Springs, NevadaStopped off in Indian Springs to get some alien memorabilia for Andy.

properties.name: The Front Gate of Hell
properties.description: Posted by MisternaxalAmargosa Valley, NevadaDeath Valley. I see why they call it Death Valley now!

properties.name: The Hills Have Eyes
properties.description: Posted by MisternaxalMercury, NevadaPortal to the Nevada Test Site, Mercury ain\'t much to look at but for a history buff it\'s pretty amazing.
